arChildNodes.szComment:
The HERO approaches NAFAIN, who is impaled upside down on a tree.
Blood stains his body and a pool of it has gathered at the base of the tree.
Nafain is in pain and he comes across as almost a husk of himself, weak and sapped of strength.
His voice is RASPY and LABORED, like it takes effort just to speak.
The old druid’s SPEAR is nearby, jutting from the ground.
Nafain’s companion, the WHITE WOLF, watches from the periphery.
Nafain deflates, puts his hand to the wood jutting from his chest. His hands come away covered in blood. He stares at them.
Cocking his head toward the weapon
The Hero yanks the spear from the ground and approaches Nafain.
The Hero JAMS THE SPEAR INTO NAFAIN’S HEART and leaves it there.

The Wolf paws up to the base of the tree and stays there.
It lets out MOURNFUL HOWLS over the loss of its master.
